1
00:01:30,360 --> 00:01:37,440
=Have a Crush on You=

2
00:01:38,020 --> 00:01:40,980
=Episode 14=

3
00:02:21,690 --> 00:02:22,450
Here by yourself?

4
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,720
I'll drink with you.

5
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:29,450
You came to a place like this.

6
00:02:29,450 --> 00:02:31,640
Don't bother playing innocent.

7
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:34,250
Beat it.

8
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,000
You've got an attitude.

9
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,610
The night is still young.

10
00:02:38,050 --> 00:02:39,170
It's too early to sleep.

11
00:02:39,530 --> 00:02:41,280
Let's have a nice chat.

12
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,170
Don't touch me!

13
00:02:44,050 --> 00:02:44,920
You're really feisty.

14
00:02:48,330 --> 00:02:49,050
Good.

15
00:02:49,050 --> 00:02:50,330
I like a woman with an attitude.

16
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,000
Do you know him?

17
00:02:53,890 --> 00:02:54,890
You have a boyfriend?

18
00:02:55,170 --> 00:02:56,250
Why are you here

19
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:57,760
if you already have a boyfriend?

20
00:02:58,450 --> 00:02:59,450
That's enough.

21
00:02:59,450 --> 00:03:00,970
What? Do you want to beat him up?

22
00:03:01,690 --> 00:03:02,000
Well.

23
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,280
Do you think you're invincible

24
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,480
just because you know a few moves?

25
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,280
That guy was asking for it.

26
00:03:08,890 --> 00:03:10,330
I was about to throw him
over the shoulder

27
00:03:10,330 --> 00:03:11,530
on the counter.

28
00:03:11,810 --> 00:03:13,450
Sure.

29
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:15,760
Stop drinking.

30
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,000
It's 58 yuan a bottle.

31
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,530
How many bottles have you already had?

32
00:03:18,530 --> 00:03:19,610
174 yuan.

33
00:03:19,610 --> 00:03:20,640
232 yuan...

34
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:22,050
I'm not making you pay the bill.

35
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,050
No?

36
00:03:23,530 --> 00:03:24,170
Cheers.

37
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,330
Come on. Let's dance.

38
00:03:30,330 --> 00:03:31,250
Dancing is free.

39
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,560
I don't want to dance.

40
00:03:34,250 --> 00:03:35,250
Dr. Ding,

41
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,170
getting drunk

42
00:03:36,170 --> 00:03:37,840
because your love
is unrequited is immature.

43
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:38,810
You're a doctor.

44
00:03:38,810 --> 00:03:40,920
Do you really believe
that alcohol can numb you?

45
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:42,280
By the time it actually does,

46
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,720
you could have got alcohol poisoning.

47
00:03:45,480 --> 00:03:46,530
If you get too drunk,

48
00:03:46,530 --> 00:03:48,120
I'll need to carry you home.

49
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:49,090
I've never got drunk

50
00:03:49,090 --> 00:03:50,410
in my life.

51
00:03:51,050 --> 00:03:52,120
You're so drunk

52
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:53,200
that you're talking nonsense.

53
00:03:53,890 --> 00:03:54,890
Listen.

54
00:03:55,610 --> 00:03:56,450
I love

55
00:03:56,450 --> 00:03:58,000
the taste of alcohol.

56
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,720
The smell of alcohol

57
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:01,920
gets me excited.

58
00:04:02,250 --> 00:04:03,720
Do you know what my dad told me?

59
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,120
That I was born for this job.

60
00:04:07,360 --> 00:04:08,450
You've got a gift.

61
00:04:09,530 --> 00:04:10,360
Well,

62
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:12,410
you and Ning are a good match.

63
00:04:13,890 --> 00:04:15,560
Will it kill you not to bring him up?

64
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,010
If I don't say that,

65
00:04:17,010 --> 00:04:18,850
will you be able to get over it?

66
00:04:20,010 --> 00:04:20,730
Yes.

67
00:04:20,850 --> 00:04:21,970
Ning is talented,

68
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:23,010
and his skills are excellent.

69
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,040
But Dr. Ding,

70
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:24,810
have you considered

71
00:04:24,810 --> 00:04:26,730
that maybe you don't actually like him?

72
00:04:26,730 --> 00:04:28,290
Maybe you just want to conquer him?

73
00:04:30,090 --> 00:04:31,010
What do you mean?

74
00:04:31,290 --> 00:04:32,810
You're talented,

75
00:04:32,810 --> 00:04:33,480
and you're used

76
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:35,250
to being better
than everyone around you.

77
00:04:35,570 --> 00:04:37,690
Ning Zhiqian is one of the best men

78
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,640
around you except me.

79
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:41,530
So you want to conquer him

80
00:04:41,530 --> 00:04:43,040
to prove your capability.

81
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,410
Why else would you want

82
00:04:44,410 --> 00:04:45,530
to be with an ice block?

83
00:04:45,690 --> 00:04:46,600
What are you after?

84
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,130
I'm on fire.

85
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,760
I have a fire in me

86
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:50,920
that I can't put out.

87
00:04:51,530 --> 00:04:52,530
I need some ice

88
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:53,570
to cool me down.

89
00:04:55,730 --> 00:04:56,410
Excuse me,

90
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:57,880
two cold drinks.

91
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,090
Here.

92
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:12,920
It's Liuzheng.

93
00:05:15,290 --> 00:05:16,290
(Hello? Liuzheng?)

94
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:17,530
I'm being held up outside.

95
00:05:17,530 --> 00:05:18,130
You guys eat first.

96
00:05:18,130 --> 00:05:19,090
Don't wait for me.

97
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,410
(All right. Okay.)

98
00:05:20,850 --> 00:05:22,290
(Your parents are hungry too.)

99
00:05:24,010 --> 00:05:25,010
Sorry.

100
00:05:25,690 --> 00:05:26,290
It's fine.

101
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,760
I'll play the chess
with Mr. Ruan after dinner.

102
00:05:29,290 --> 00:05:29,920
I'll wait for you.

103
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:32,600
I might be home really late tonight.

104
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:33,730
You really don't have to wait for me.

105
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:34,920
It's fine.

106
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:35,920
I'll wait however long you need.

107
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,250
Liuzheng,

108
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:40,970
we haven't seen each other

109
00:05:40,970 --> 00:05:42,040
in almost a week.

110
00:05:44,130 --> 00:05:45,040
Here. Put this on.

111
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:46,920
Ning Xiang,

112
00:05:47,290 --> 00:05:48,360
go get your mother.

113
00:05:48,730 --> 00:05:49,690
It's time to blow out the candles.

114
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:54,730
Mom.

115
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:57,600
Dad is waiting for you
to blow out the candles.

116
00:05:58,810 --> 00:05:59,920
Okay. I'll be right there.

117
00:06:01,090 --> 00:06:02,130
I'm hanging up.

118
00:06:02,130 --> 00:06:02,730
Bye.

119
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:06,600
Let's not wait for her anymore.

120
00:06:06,850 --> 00:06:07,640
Let's eat first.

121
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,410
Yes.

122
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:09,160
Let's eat.

123
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,250
Here, Mr. Ruan.

124
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:23,540
(Happy Birthday)

125
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:28,530
Make a wish.

126
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:36,850
Dad,

127
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,690
make a wish.

128
00:06:39,690 --> 00:06:40,290
I'm not a kid.

129
00:06:40,290 --> 00:06:40,970
I don't need to make a wish.

130
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:41,920
Just make a wish.

131
00:06:42,810 --> 00:06:44,090
Dad, wait.

132
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:45,850
Since you don't want to make a wish,

133
00:06:45,850 --> 00:06:48,320
let's play a game.

134
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:51,640
A game? What game?

135
00:06:53,290 --> 00:06:55,530
Truth or dare.

136
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:57,640
How do you play that game?

137
00:06:58,320 --> 00:07:00,040
Rock, paper, scissors.

138
00:07:00,410 --> 00:07:03,850
The loser gets punished.

139
00:07:03,880 --> 00:07:04,480
Okay.

140
00:07:05,010 --> 00:07:05,600
Come on.

141
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:09,090
Rock, paper, scissors.

142
00:07:10,010 --> 00:07:11,880
You lost, Dad.

143
00:07:12,730 --> 00:07:13,480
Choose.

144
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,920
Truth or dare?

145
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,480
Dare.

146
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,320
Okay.

147
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:22,320
Your dare

148
00:07:22,410 --> 00:07:24,160
is to kiss Mom.

149
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,090
Change it.

150
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,320
Can I do something else?

151
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:35,130
I'll pick truth instead.

152
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:35,970
Okay.

153
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:38,410
Mom,

154
00:07:38,410 --> 00:07:40,880
is there anything you want to ask Dad?

155
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:47,690
Mr. Ning.

156
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:51,410
Do you think

157
00:07:51,410 --> 00:07:52,530
I'm a qualified doctor?

158
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:54,880
Yes.

159
00:07:56,440 --> 00:07:57,320
Mom, Dad,

160
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:59,040
let's play another round.

161
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,090
Okay.

162
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,090
Come on.

163
00:08:01,410 --> 00:08:03,480
Rock, paper, scissors.

164
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,690
Mom, you lost.

165
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:09,250
Truth or dare?

166
00:08:10,130 --> 00:08:11,290
Truth.

167
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,320
I'll ask the question.

168
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:18,090
Do you still like Dad?

169
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:32,850
You have to answer truthfully.

170
00:08:32,850 --> 00:08:34,800
Lying is wrong.

171
00:08:36,530 --> 00:08:37,240
Hurry up and blow out the candles.

172
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,370
They're going to burn the cake.

173
00:08:39,170 --> 00:08:41,410
No, Dad.

174
00:08:41,410 --> 00:08:43,560
Mom agreed to play.

175
00:08:43,560 --> 00:08:46,850
So she has to follow the rules.

176
00:08:49,410 --> 00:08:50,680
Mom,

177
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:52,930
do you still like Dad?

178
00:09:23,290 --> 00:09:23,850
Hello?

179
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:31,320
I...

180
00:09:34,170 --> 00:09:35,320
I don't dare to anymore.

181
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,050
What do we do?

182
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,290
Do you have any other ideas?

183
00:09:57,930 --> 00:09:58,730
No.

184
00:10:24,050 --> 00:10:24,930
Dr. Ding,

185
00:10:25,050 --> 00:10:26,610
I think I'm getting alcohol poisoning.

186
00:10:26,610 --> 00:10:28,240
Let's stop drinking and go home.

187
00:10:28,410 --> 00:10:29,800
Go home by yourself.

188
00:10:30,640 --> 00:10:32,410
Can you not be so stubborn?

189
00:10:32,410 --> 00:10:33,530
Ning Zhiqian

190
00:10:33,610 --> 00:10:36,000
is basically Mount Everest.

191
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,240
He's so high.

192
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,680
Why do you want to hike him?

193
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:39,680
He's not the only mountain

194
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,970
in the world.

195
00:10:40,970 --> 00:10:42,370
Why can't you climb another mountain?

196
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,320
Climb...

197
00:10:44,050 --> 00:10:45,120
Climb me instead.

198
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:45,850
Just one day.

199
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:46,880
No.

200
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,290
I'll let you climb to my peak right now.

201
00:10:48,290 --> 00:10:48,880
Come on.

202
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:51,170
I'm not interested in a mound

203
00:10:51,170 --> 00:10:52,730
like you.

204
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:58,780
(Chunyan)

205
00:11:00,490 --> 00:11:01,560
I need to take this call.

206
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:02,530
Don't drink too much.

207
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:17,170
Buddy!

208
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:19,320
Are you okay?

209
00:11:20,240 --> 00:11:20,850
Buddy!

210
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:22,050
What's going on?

211
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:23,000
Is there a doctor in the house?

212
00:11:24,610 --> 00:11:25,200
Buddy!

213
00:11:26,170 --> 00:11:27,120
Is there a doctor here?

214
00:11:27,490 --> 00:11:28,410
Do we have a doctor?

215
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:30,170
Let me through.

216
00:11:30,170 --> 00:11:31,050
Is there a doctor?

217
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,240
I'm a doctor. What happened?

218
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:33,970
He was fine just now.

219
00:11:34,090 --> 00:11:34,850
Then, he collapsed all of a sudden.

220
00:11:34,850 --> 00:11:35,530
Wake up.

221
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:37,370
Did he show any symptoms
before he collapsed?

222
00:11:37,850 --> 00:11:38,930
He coughed a few times violently.

223
00:11:39,090 --> 00:11:40,410
Did he have any lung problems?

224
00:11:40,850 --> 00:11:41,560
He had ï»¿emphysema.

225
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,370
I visited him
in the hospital last month.

226
00:11:46,050 --> 00:11:47,050
Did anyone call ambulance?

227
00:11:47,370 --> 00:11:48,000
Yes.

228
00:11:48,610 --> 00:11:49,530
What's the ETA?

229
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,050
The emergency lane
was blocked by a private vehicle.

230
00:11:52,050 --> 00:11:53,050
The ambulance can't pass through.

231
00:11:53,850 --> 00:11:54,410
Doctor,

232
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:55,610
what do we do?

233
00:11:56,490 --> 00:11:57,050
Doctor,

234
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,370
you have to save my friend!

235
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,880
I need a few items.

236
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:02,730
Liquor with high alcohol content,
disposable gloves,

237
00:12:02,730 --> 00:12:04,200
a straw, and a fruit knife.

238
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:04,800
Okay.

239
00:12:04,800 --> 00:12:05,290
Doctor,

240
00:12:05,370 --> 00:12:06,370
you have to save my friend.

241
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:07,370
He's only 35.

242
00:12:07,370 --> 00:12:08,120
Calm down.

243
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,170
It's most likely a pneumothorax attack.

244
00:12:09,170 --> 00:12:09,880
He has the heartbeat,

245
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:10,850
but he isn't breathing.

246
00:12:10,850 --> 00:12:11,530
I'll think of something.

247
00:12:12,050 --> 00:12:12,490
Okay.

248
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:16,370
The items you requested.

249
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:21,120
What's your name?

250
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:23,680
What's your name?

251
00:13:24,530 --> 00:13:25,530
Qiu Yifei.

252
00:13:26,170 --> 00:13:26,880
Thank you.

253
00:13:27,050 --> 00:13:27,640
Thank you, Doctor.

254
00:13:27,970 --> 00:13:28,730
Thank you, Doctor.

255
00:13:29,090 --> 00:13:29,850
Thank you, Doctor.

256
00:13:30,050 --> 00:13:31,490
Great!

257
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:32,680
Wonderful!

258
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:33,410
Amazing!

259
00:13:33,610 --> 00:13:34,440
Impressive!

260
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:35,680
Great!

261
00:13:37,990 --> 00:13:38,900
That was incredible.

262
00:14:16,170 --> 00:14:16,970
Dad,

263
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:18,090
does Mom

264
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:19,930
have a boyfriend?

265
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:24,760
Don't worry about adult matters.

266
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:26,000
Focus on your studies.

267
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,240
So

268
00:14:30,170 --> 00:14:31,410
she does have a boyfriend?

269
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,170
How would I know?

270
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:35,970
Go back to your room.

271
00:14:35,970 --> 00:14:36,560
Go.

272
00:14:44,680 --> 00:14:45,880
I've never seen Ning Xiang so happy

273
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:47,640
as he is today.

274
00:14:48,290 --> 00:14:49,410
It's different

275
00:14:49,610 --> 00:14:50,930
when a child has a mother.

276
00:14:52,410 --> 00:14:53,680
Well.

277
00:14:53,970 --> 00:14:54,930
How far have Liuzheng and that man

278
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:56,120
got?

279
00:14:56,320 --> 00:14:57,000
Do you know?

280
00:14:58,050 --> 00:14:59,120
I really don't.

281
00:14:59,610 --> 00:15:00,490
It's late.

282
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:01,680
Go home.

283
00:15:01,970 --> 00:15:04,290
I'm just concerned for your sake.

284
00:15:05,570 --> 00:15:07,420
Liuzheng is a good woman.

285
00:15:07,420 --> 00:15:08,000
Seven years ago,

286
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,200
you drove her away.

287
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,240
Now, she's finally back.

288
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:12,680
As your father,

289
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:13,680
I should support you

290
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:14,440
and cheer you on,

291
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,120
right?

292
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,000
She said

293
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:19,050
she didn't dare to like you anymore.

294
00:15:19,410 --> 00:15:20,320
That means

295
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:21,610
she does like you,

296
00:15:21,730 --> 00:15:22,930
but she's afraid.

297
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,090
What do you think she's afraid of?

298
00:15:26,120 --> 00:15:26,760
Ning Xiang!

299
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,290
Grandpa is leaving.

300
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,290
See him out.

301
00:15:30,970 --> 00:15:32,850
Is Grandpa leaving?

302
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:35,610
Yes.

303
00:15:36,610 --> 00:15:38,090
I'll see you this weekend.

304
00:15:38,090 --> 00:15:39,200
I'll make you delicious food.

305
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,530
I'm taking him out this weekend.

306
00:15:40,930 --> 00:15:42,120
Also, please call me

307
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:44,320
before you come over next time.

308
00:15:51,090 --> 00:15:51,730
Let's go.

309
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:55,760
Grandpa.

310
00:15:56,530 --> 00:15:59,200
I want to enjoy your cooking
this weekend.

311
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:00,970
Next time.

312
00:16:00,970 --> 00:16:02,680
I'll prepare delicious food for you.

313
00:16:03,850 --> 00:16:05,120
Take care on your way home.

314
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:06,090
Grandpa,

315
00:16:06,200 --> 00:16:07,490
when will you come again?

316
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:09,240
If you miss me,

317
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,240
just give me a call,

318
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:11,170
and I'll come right over.

319
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:15,490
Oh, right.

320
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:16,800
Remember

321
00:16:17,290 --> 00:16:18,730
to tell your father

322
00:16:20,090 --> 00:16:21,090
what

323
00:16:21,610 --> 00:16:22,730
I told you.

324
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:24,930
Okay.

325
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:26,490
Goodbye.

326
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:27,850
Take care on your way home.

327
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:29,490
Bye.

328
00:16:29,490 --> 00:16:30,970
Bye. Take care on your way home.

329
00:16:30,970 --> 00:16:31,730
Okay.

330
00:16:32,050 --> 00:16:33,120
Bye.

331
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:40,730
Son,

332
00:16:41,090 --> 00:16:42,240
happy birthday.

333
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,200
Who are you calling "son"?

334
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:47,530
Grandpa told me to say that.

335
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:48,880
He said

336
00:16:48,880 --> 00:16:51,240
he didn't get to say that to you today.

337
00:16:51,610 --> 00:16:54,610
So he wanted me to say it for him.

338
00:16:57,610 --> 00:16:58,640
Son,

339
00:16:58,680 --> 00:16:59,800
happy birthday.

340
00:17:01,530 --> 00:17:03,050
Come here. Sit down.

341
00:17:03,240 --> 00:17:03,930
Sit.

342
00:17:04,890 --> 00:17:05,680
Dad,

343
00:17:06,130 --> 00:17:08,400
I have something important to tell you.

344
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:09,440
Go ahead.

345
00:17:11,010 --> 00:17:12,130
Can you not be

346
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:15,090
so mean to Grandpa?

347
00:17:15,650 --> 00:17:16,890
You're so mean.

348
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,130
Grandpa, Mom,

349
00:17:19,130 --> 00:17:20,400
and I

350
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:22,040
are afraid of you.

351
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:24,400
We dare not like you anymore.

352
00:17:28,610 --> 00:17:29,680
Was I mean to your mother?

353
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:31,160
Yes.

354
00:17:31,560 --> 00:17:33,250
Was I mean to you and your grandfather?

355
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:34,090
Yes.

356
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,560
Was I?

357
00:17:35,560 --> 00:17:36,770
Yes!

358
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:39,320
Really?

359
00:17:40,490 --> 00:17:42,560
One day, you...

360
00:17:42,920 --> 00:17:43,520
Okay.

361
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:44,730
I'll be nicer to you from now on,

362
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:45,440
okay?

363
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:46,090
Okay.

364
00:17:46,090 --> 00:17:47,160
Will you be a good boy?

365
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:48,090
Yes.

366
00:18:05,490 --> 00:18:05,970
Liuzheng.

367
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,130
Mr. Xue.

368
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:09,920
Why are you...

369
00:18:10,370 --> 00:18:10,920
I was waiting for you.

370
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:14,200
Let's take a walk.

371
00:18:16,280 --> 00:18:16,890
Okay.

372
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:25,650
From what you're saying,

373
00:18:26,490 --> 00:18:27,800
Mr. Ning is a good man.

374
00:18:28,370 --> 00:18:29,920
No wonder you've been going
to his place lately.

375
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:31,200
It was for his son.

376
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:33,010
I'm really sorry

377
00:18:33,200 --> 00:18:33,970
for missing our arrangement.

378
00:18:34,250 --> 00:18:34,850
It's fine.

379
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:36,010
No need to be sorry.

380
00:18:37,370 --> 00:18:38,850
I'm a surgeon.

381
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:40,850
I need to work overtime often.

382
00:18:40,850 --> 00:18:41,650
If something comes up at the hospital,

383
00:18:41,650 --> 00:18:42,730
I'll need to be there right away.

384
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:44,560
Most people find that hard to accept.

385
00:18:44,770 --> 00:18:46,610
Well, as you said,
it's just most people.

386
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:48,560
Ever since I spent
the Mid-Autumn Festival with you

387
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,040
at the hospital,

388
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:51,730
I've been captivated

389
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:52,800
by your image

390
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:53,610
as an angel in white.

391
00:18:54,970 --> 00:18:56,130
It's just my job.

392
00:18:56,130 --> 00:18:57,490
Don't put me on such a high pedestal.

393
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,490
You're a good catch.

394
00:19:00,490 --> 00:19:01,370
I'm sure you have a lot

395
00:19:01,370 --> 00:19:02,200
of female admirers.

396
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:05,250
But you're the only one I have eyes for.

397
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,730
I'm busy with work every day.

398
00:19:12,090 --> 00:19:13,890
And I'm at the stage where
I'm moving up the ladder in my career.

399
00:19:14,490 --> 00:19:15,130
I don't want

400
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:16,250
to be distracted by a relationship.

401
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:18,130
I know.

402
00:19:18,370 --> 00:19:20,250
I know
you're on the rise in your career.

403
00:19:20,770 --> 00:19:21,610
Don't worry.

404
00:19:21,730 --> 00:19:23,040
I won't hold you back.

405
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:30,130
It's late.

406
00:19:30,610 --> 00:19:31,730
Why don't I walk you home?

407
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:34,320
Let's go.

408
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,040
Oh, right.

409
00:19:41,730 --> 00:19:42,440
The lawsuit

410
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:43,520
is going to trial soon.

411
00:19:47,020 --> 00:19:52,580
(Beiya Hospital)

412
00:19:52,580 --> 00:19:56,660
(First-aid Room, Emergency Department)

413
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:00,730
Your vitals look fine,

414
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:02,440
mister.

415
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,130
Everything is normal.

416
00:20:03,610 --> 00:20:04,440
You're out of the woods.

417
00:20:06,250 --> 00:20:07,130
Take him to the observation room later.

418
00:20:07,130 --> 00:20:08,200
If everything's fine here, we can go.

419
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:09,320
Let's go.

420
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:13,160
I heard you guys rescued him.

421
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:15,770
Did you two insert that straw?

422
00:20:15,770 --> 00:20:16,850
I did it.

423
00:20:18,730 --> 00:20:20,370
That was very professional

424
00:20:20,370 --> 00:20:21,400
and timely.

425
00:20:21,920 --> 00:20:23,160
Did you know this?

426
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,800
He was lucky to have you guys there.

427
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:25,320
Any later,

428
00:20:25,320 --> 00:20:26,280
he would've lost his life.

429
00:20:27,650 --> 00:20:29,010
Are you two doctors too?

430
00:20:29,090 --> 00:20:30,320
Yes, we're from
the Neurosurgery Department.

431
00:20:30,920 --> 00:20:31,920
Beiya as well?

432
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:32,520
Yes.

433
00:20:32,850 --> 00:20:34,250
I'm a resident, Ding Yiyuan.

434
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:35,320
I just returned from overseas.

435
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,850
He is the famous Cheng Zhouyu

436
00:20:36,850 --> 00:20:37,920
of the Neurosurgery Department.

437
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,130
Don't you know him?

438
00:20:39,370 --> 00:20:41,160
I just got back from overseas too.

439
00:20:41,320 --> 00:20:42,890
I'm new at Beiya as well.

440
00:20:42,890 --> 00:20:44,040
Let's introduce ourselves.

441
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,400
I'm Xie Haojie.

442
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,320
I'm the attending doctor
of the Thoracic Surgery Department.

443
00:20:47,010 --> 00:20:47,370
Dr. Xie.

444
00:20:47,370 --> 00:20:48,010
Nice to meet you.

445
00:20:48,010 --> 00:20:49,010
Hello. It's nice to meet you.

446
00:20:49,010 --> 00:20:50,370
I'll go get busy.

447
00:20:50,370 --> 00:20:51,730
Let's meet up another day.

448
00:20:51,730 --> 00:20:52,440
- Okay.
- All right.

449
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:53,160
- Goodbye, Dr. Xie.
- Thanks.

450
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:53,650
Bye.

451
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,090
Let's go.

452
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:58,970
Did you hear him?

453
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:01,010
Dr. Xie said I saved that man.

454
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:02,370
(Emergency)
Yes. You did.

455
00:21:02,370 --> 00:21:03,560
Good work, Dr. Ding.

456
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:06,490
It feels great
to be a doctor and save lives.

457
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:08,440
Come on.

458
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:09,850
Let's find another place for round two.

459
00:21:09,970 --> 00:21:10,890
No, I'm done.

460
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,280
I'm not upset anymore.

461
00:21:12,610 --> 00:21:14,130
I realized that unrequited love

462
00:21:14,130 --> 00:21:15,970
is such a trivial matter.

463
00:21:16,890 --> 00:21:17,920
So you're done

464
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:19,010
moping over Ning?

465
00:21:19,490 --> 00:21:20,890
What else can I do?

466
00:21:20,890 --> 00:21:22,730
I can't crack open his head

467
00:21:22,850 --> 00:21:24,250
and check what's wrong with him

468
00:21:24,250 --> 00:21:25,400
for not returning my feelings, right?

469
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,490
Actually, you were right.

470
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:30,560
I don't know anything about him.

471
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:31,800
I like him

472
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,090
because

473
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:34,010
he is the best man

474
00:21:34,010 --> 00:21:36,010
within a 50-meter radius

475
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:37,650
of me.

476
00:21:37,730 --> 00:21:38,370
Yes.

477
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:41,040
But don't you think

478
00:21:41,040 --> 00:21:42,440
you got over him a little too fast?

479
00:21:43,250 --> 00:21:45,130
I was cured by that guy I saved.

480
00:21:46,800 --> 00:21:48,040
Who's the doctor,

481
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:48,650
and who's the patient here?

482
00:21:48,650 --> 00:21:49,890
Who saved whom?

483
00:21:49,890 --> 00:21:51,370
We healed each other.

484
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:52,160
Let's go.

485
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,770
We need to perform outpatient duty
early morning tomorrow.

486
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:56,610
Thanks for today.

487
00:21:57,560 --> 00:21:58,440
Don't say things like that.

488
00:21:58,440 --> 00:21:59,280
I'm not used to it.

489
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,010
I'll treat you to a meal next time,

490
00:22:01,010 --> 00:22:01,920
Mr. Cheng.

491
00:22:02,200 --> 00:22:03,040
Talk properly.

492
00:22:03,130 --> 00:22:03,970
Don't mock me.

493
00:22:05,010 --> 00:22:06,280
Who is mocking you?

494
00:22:24,680 --> 00:22:25,440
Good morning.

495
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:26,850
Good morning.

496
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:27,250
Good morning.

497
00:22:27,250 --> 00:22:28,320
Good morning, Mr. Ning.

498
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:28,970
Good morning.

499
00:22:31,320 --> 00:22:32,970
I have an announcement to make.

500
00:22:33,130 --> 00:22:34,280
From today onwards,

501
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:36,130
I no longer have feelings for Mr. Ning.

502
00:22:38,250 --> 00:22:39,160
Is she changing the male lead?

503
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:42,560
Dr. Cheng,

504
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,370
you might be moving up.

505
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:46,850
Time to make the rounds.

506
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:06,200
Let's go.

507
00:23:06,370 --> 00:23:07,010
Let's make the rounds.

508
00:23:15,890 --> 00:23:16,890
Why did you need to see me so urgently?

509
00:23:17,010 --> 00:23:18,090
I have a meeting later.

510
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:20,090
Your father asked me
to drink with him two days ago.

511
00:23:20,090 --> 00:23:21,440
He cried.

512
00:23:22,650 --> 00:23:24,490
How embarrassing for a man of his age.

513
00:23:24,770 --> 00:23:25,610
What was he crying about?

514
00:23:25,650 --> 00:23:26,770
Well, he regretted what he did.

515
00:23:26,890 --> 00:23:28,490
He thinks the way you treat him now

516
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:29,650
is as good as you've disowned him.

517
00:23:29,970 --> 00:23:30,770
Xiao'er,

518
00:23:30,890 --> 00:23:32,730
if you're here
to put in a good word for him,

519
00:23:32,730 --> 00:23:34,010
don't bother.

520
00:23:34,010 --> 00:23:35,400
- Hello, Mr. Xue.
- I won't forgive him.

521
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:36,680
Why are you like this

522
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:37,650
whenever your father is brought up?

523
00:23:38,490 --> 00:23:38,890
Have a seat.

524
00:23:38,890 --> 00:23:39,280
Thanks.

525
00:23:40,090 --> 00:23:41,200
Why is Liuzheng here?

526
00:23:41,610 --> 00:23:42,560
Did you call her here?

527
00:23:43,970 --> 00:23:44,400
I deliberately

528
00:23:44,610 --> 00:23:45,490
found a restaurant

529
00:23:45,490 --> 00:23:46,440
closer to your hospital.

530
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:49,160
Be discreet.

531
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:53,610
Isn't that Xue Weilin from Zhanying?

532
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:56,440
Take a look at this.

533
00:23:57,010 --> 00:23:58,890
Why is Liuzheng with Xue Weilin?

534
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:02,040
No wonder

535
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:03,610
you asked me about that guy.

536
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:04,920
So it had to do with Liuzheng.

537
00:24:06,250 --> 00:24:08,130
The result of the case is out so soon?

538
00:24:08,610 --> 00:24:09,770
If we followed the legal process,

539
00:24:09,770 --> 00:24:10,800
certainly it's not so soon.

540
00:24:11,090 --> 00:24:12,090
But Zhang Lei didn't want
to continue the lawsuit.

541
00:24:12,090 --> 00:24:13,320
She looks happy.

542
00:24:14,250 --> 00:24:15,520
He agreed to issue a public apology.

543
00:24:16,090 --> 00:24:16,680
And...

544
00:24:18,770 --> 00:24:19,440
Is she?

545
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:21,730
Looking at it again,
I think that smile looks forced.

546
00:24:25,490 --> 00:24:26,090
This is

547
00:24:26,090 --> 00:24:27,250
the most he could afford.

548
00:24:28,130 --> 00:24:29,520
If we continue,

549
00:24:29,520 --> 00:24:30,890
how much will the court award?

550
00:24:31,370 --> 00:24:32,490
There is no clear legal standard

551
00:24:32,490 --> 00:24:34,200
for damage for loss of reputation.

552
00:24:34,770 --> 00:24:36,010
But from my experience,

553
00:24:36,160 --> 00:24:37,850
it won't be more than this amount.

554
00:24:39,890 --> 00:24:40,490
All right.

555
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,130
Why is Xue Weilin giving Liuzheng money?

556
00:24:44,650 --> 00:24:46,160
He's helping her with a case

557
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:47,440
that concerns damage to her reputation.

558
00:24:48,090 --> 00:24:48,730
I'm a lawyer too.

559
00:24:48,730 --> 00:24:49,490
Why didn't she ask me for help?

560
00:24:49,770 --> 00:24:50,610
Lie low.

561
00:24:52,610 --> 00:24:54,200
She probably thinks
you're not good enough.

562
00:24:54,370 --> 00:24:55,730
Not good enough?

563
00:24:55,730 --> 00:24:56,970
Xue Weilin and I

564
00:24:56,970 --> 00:24:59,400
are equally matched.

565
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:01,010
I'm not better than him,

566
00:25:01,010 --> 00:25:02,440
but we're evenly matched,
at the very least.

567
00:25:02,610 --> 00:25:03,770
Then, you're probably too garrulous.

568
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,010
What was that?

569
00:25:09,490 --> 00:25:10,400
Watch your tone.

570
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,320
And you say you're not garrulous.

571
00:25:20,140 --> 00:25:25,180
(Beiya Hospital)

572
00:25:27,940 --> 00:25:29,740
(Self-payment, Cai Jinrong,
Remaining amount to be paid: RMB18,563)

573
00:25:29,740 --> 00:25:30,180
(Pay with card)

574
00:25:31,770 --> 00:25:33,650
I still need to pay so much?

575
00:25:38,580 --> 00:25:39,980
(Insufficient balance,
please try another card)

576
00:25:41,730 --> 00:25:42,680
Not enough.

577
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:46,090
This.

578
00:25:46,090 --> 00:25:47,320
(Insufficient balance,
please try another card)

579
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:47,800
Ma'am,

580
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:48,730
can you hurry up?

581
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:50,160
Oh, okay.

582
00:25:50,490 --> 00:25:51,090
You go first.

583
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,560
What do I do?

584
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:11,890
Juan,

585
00:26:12,090 --> 00:26:12,800
what's wrong?

586
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,610
I... I don't have enough money.

